      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAYDAY MAYDAY (1) jumped from this box last time and placed in a Grade 6 at this track over 381m, finishing third (22.29). Has a very consistent record off this same box, including two wins and eight placings from 19 starts. Looks the one to beat on best. QUEEN POTATO (8) charged out of the boxes with a slick early split and went straight to the front, giving a huge sight but headed late when a 1.75 lengths second (22.20) over 381m at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Expected to be in this for a long way. LIKE A FERRARI (2) jumped from the inside and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten half a length (16.42) behind Liberty Star at this track. Expected to be in this for a long way. REPRIEVAL (7) is new to this circuit but can play a major role.",
